---
import DocLayout from '@/layouts/DocLayout.astro'
import { productFacts } from '@/lib/facts'
---

<DocLayout
  title="Crawler"
  description="Inspect technical SEO evidence page by page, save the result locally, and compare it after a deploy."
>
  <h2>Run a crawl</h2>
  <pre><code>seo crawl https://example.com --format pretty</code></pre>
  <p>Use a project profile when you have one:</p>
  <pre><code>seo crawl --project example --max-pages 500</code></pre>

  <h2>What it records</h2>
  <p>
    The crawler records response and redirect data, indexability, canonicals,
    titles, descriptions, headings, links, images, structured data, hreflang,
    mobile configuration, security headers, social previews, and performance
    observations. Its {productFacts.crawlerRules} documented rules have stable
    IDs, severity, evidence fields, repair guidance, and verification steps.
  </p>
  <pre><code>seo rules
seo explain --rule missing_meta_description</code></pre>

  <h2>Control the work</h2>
  <p>
    Useful limits include <code>--max-pages</code>, <code>--max-depth</code>,
    <code>--include</code>, <code>--exclude</code>, <code>--no-sitemap</code>, and
    <code>--no-external</code>. Robots.txt is respected by default.
  </p>

  <h2>Save and compare</h2>
  <pre><code>seo crawl --project example --save
seo crawl-reports
seo crawl-reports --compare latest --against previous</code></pre>
  <p>
    Comparisons show added, removed, fixed, and changed pages, plus rule and
    health movement. Reusing a saved report also lets an agent inspect affected
    URLs or top fixes without crawling again.
  </p>

  <h2>Choose an output</h2>
  <pre><code>seo crawl https://example.com --format json
seo crawl https://example.com --format csv --csv issues
seo crawl https://example.com --format html --output report.html
seo crawl https://example.com --format markdown --output tickets.md</code></pre>

  <h2>Gate a deployment</h2>
  <pre><code>seo crawl https://example.com --fail-on high --json</code></pre>
  <p>
    The command exits unsuccessfully when findings meet the chosen severity,
    while the JSON output preserves the evidence that caused the gate to fail.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
